 SK's, OH MY!!</span><hr size=1> Hehe, hey all, I'd just like to say my peice. Kinda kewl we got a forum for us half breeds, but it seems there are some down spirits about our class!<br>
First of all, ya, we got that xp penalty slapped on our ass and we are stuck with it. But ya know why? It's cause we kick so much ass over the other classes! I mean, cmon. Paladins: What better tank? We DONT need a healer, we are very self sufficient, two of us can make up for one cleric (ya get two half assed healers -which makes one ass, and that's good- and two tanks!). We have great weapons! We have rooting/stun/healing! Did I mention a tank with kick ass healing? hehe Paladins, they are great, any other tank has to either sit on his ass for days (warriors), go into combat AGAIN and lifetap his way to a healthy new life (SK's), or grow a beard casting those teeny ranger-heals (guess). Paladins are great.. but....(I'll get to our downsides in a sec)<br>
Rangers!! ta daaa! Thought I was going to bash on them, didn't ya? hehe.. well, maybe later. There is always time for Ranger-Bashing. BUT, they ARE good, IF played right ;P<br>
Rangers make GREAT backup tanks. Just so long as they don't over taunt and stress out the cleric, they work perfectly. I always tell my wife to remove her fbss so I don't have to taunt from a Flux-Bladed-Yak weilding hasted superwoman all the time. She doesn't do as much damage, but in the end we all live longer. But rangers can kite! sorta.. I love grouping with rangers, they are little sow batteries. BESIDES, Rangers aka TauntMachines are so good at taunting the mobs off clerics/enchanters that I love having my wife around so I get to keep fighting and she gets to do the pingpong of racing back and forth running after a Frog who's chasing down our Enchanter. hehe<br>
ShadowKnights... dun dun duuuuuuuuuun...<br>
My FAVORITE Hybrid. If I could restart Fenye, she'd be a SK all the way. SK's have the snaring ability of a ranger, the dot's and lifetaps of young necromancers, a PET, Harm Touch (great for KSing those named mobs that greedy droods try to take from you), as well as Invis to Undead AND Invis!! They rock! They make the best over all hybrid, and while not as good as a Paladin tank wise, they still have the same hp/ac thereabouts as a Paladin and snaring abilities. I usually try to replace the rangers in the group with SK's if we plan on doing some heavy fighting. Plus thier armor is soooo sexy ;P<br>
<br>
Ok!! Bash time!!<br>
<br>
Paladins have a hard time taunting mobs and keeping them on them selves. Too many times I am resorting to using Flash of Light, Stun, and Expulse if I can just to keep em on me. My wife goes beserk sometimes, and I peek over at her, and she's already frothing at the mouth, this hurricane of blades and feet, lightning shooting out of every finger... eesh, guess I'm sleeping on the couch tonight. We just can't taunt well enough to keep up with the damage the other classes do. Granted, we get great weapons for around our 30's, but in our late 40's we have a very hard time keeping up with the other classes like those Warriors with Mithril Staffs, those Rangers with Flux Bladed Axes, etc. After we get our super weapons, like the Fiery Avenger or Holycon Broadsword, we will once again riegn in the damage arena. But until then we will be seen as lazy slacker tanks. hehe.<br>
Rangers!! I ALWAYS  have stuff to say to Rangers!!! ooh, but it'd be like 40 pages long if I did that, so here is the small and short of it.<br>
