Besides that, my offensive ability does not make up for my lack of defense as a ranger.  This becomes painfully obvious in Kunark.  Since I have the least hp, least ac, and least defensive ability of all tanks and hybrids, why does my spell set not reflect this?  I have been stuck inbetween casting/tanking and it does not fit what I think of when I picture a ranger.  Of course, my view means little.  But I have played my ranger in every zone, and know how to play him well.  It is not a question of tactics, but the inevitable.  I cannot tank 50+, and offer nothing to a group that a different class cannot do better.  I am a mana sink for the healer, can't tank as well as the other tanks, and can't do damage to take the place of a blaster.  (no i do not outdamage everyone besides monks and rogues)  I am lucky enough to have great friends, and together we are always successfull.  The only reason I have not switched out of my ranger completely is the fact that I would have to leave my friends behind.<br>
I am not asking to be able to outdamage a warrior, or a monk, or anything.  I just want to stop being shortchanged with an xp penalty, defensive skill caps, and hp cap.  3 big things against me, and getting sow at 39 didn't make up for it.  Niether did careless lightning (99dd), or my pathetic heals.  Post 50, I hope it is not as grim as it looks.<br>
